Hi,
The wifi signal is *very* weak on lineageOS, which renders the wifi nearly unusable: The phone never reports full signal strength, even at 10 cm of the router, and the wiki connection drops if I'm, like, 5m away from the router.
This is definitely a software issue, because I don't have the issue on the stock firmware.
What I tried so far:
 * different radios: no change, as expected
 * clean install of the last 4 versions of LineageOS ,with and without Gapps: no change
 * reinstall stock firmware (full wipe): no issue on stock firmware
Some investigations:
 * the wpa supplicatant conf is slightly different on stock firmware (wpa_supplicant.conf, wpa_supplicant_overlay.conf and p2p_supplicant_overlay.conf)
 * there seems to be a lot more firmware files on stock (in etc/wifi, not vendor/firmware):
